# Theme repo map

## Source of truth vs output

| Role | Path |
| ---- | ---- |
| Edit CSS here | `themes/addons/vscode-preview/original/<family>/vscode-preview-*.css` |
| Build script | `themes/addons/vscode-preview/build-mpe-global.mjs` |
| Generated paste targets | `themes/mpe/global-*.less` |

Do **not** hand-edit `themes/mpe/global-*.less` unless the user explicitly asks. Change source CSS, then rebuild.

```bash
node themes/addons/vscode-preview/build-mpe-global.mjs
```

## Shared CSS appended by build

Always: `_scope.css`, `_syntax-tokens.css`  
Optional: `_diagram-tokens.css` (`appendDiagramTokens: true`), graphite refine (`appendSyntaxRefine: true`)

## Mermaid

- Config: `themes/mpe/mermaid-config-cpp-modern.json` → merge into Crossnote `mermaidConfig` (not whole `config.js`)
- Deep dive: `docs/mermaid-styling.md`
- Prefer config over fighting SVG with preview CSS alone

## Fixtures and iteration

- Markdown: `examples/mermaid-showcase.md`, `examples/code-showcase.md`
- Browser workbench: `preview/` — iterate UI, then hand off CSS into `original/`
- Install docs: `themes/mpe/README.md`, `themes/README.md`
